hands_on_practices.solution:
The hypercharge generator in the fundamental $\mathbf{5}$ of $SU(5)$ is traceless, with
$$Y_3=-\tfrac{2}{3},\quad Y_2=+1,\qquad3Y_3+2Y_2=0.$$
Gauge bosons in the adjoint carry $Y$-charge equal to the difference of fundamental weights.  The leptoquark connecting a quark index ($i=1,2,3$) to a lepton index ($j=4,5$) thus has
$$Y_{LQ}=Y_j - Y_i=1-(-\tfrac{2}{3})=\tfrac{5}{3},$$
which corresponds to the $(\bar{\mathbf{3}},\mathbf{2})_{5/3}$ representation, and its antiparticle transforms as $(\mathbf{3},\mathbf{2})_{-5/3}$.  Hence for the $(\bar{\mathbf{3}},\mathbf{2})_{5/3}$ leptoquark we have
$$\frac{Y}{2}=\frac{5}{6},\qquad Q=T_L^3+\frac{Y}{2},$$
so
$$T_L^3=Q-\frac{Y}{2}
=\frac{4}{3}-\frac{5}{6}
=\frac{8}{6}-\frac{5}{6}
=\frac{3}{6}
=\frac12.$$
